  <original-body>If you create an AJAX request via remote_function and specify GET as the method, the authenticity_token parameter is added even though it isn't needed. Consequently, the authenticity_token appears in some URLs such as pagination links on the following page.

This patch ensures that the parameter is not added for GET requests. It checks against js_options rather than options to avoid the confusion surrounding method_option_to_s.

This has been tested with edge and 2.0.2.</original-body>
